title: PfMP Practice Exam 02
description: Comprehensive practice test covering Governance, Stakeholder Engagement, and Life Cycle Management.

questions.text: While planning for risk management, multiple investment choice tools are used as part of the quantitative and qualitative analyzes; which of the following tools determines the effect of changing one or more factors?
questions.explanation:
c) is correct. Trade-off analysis determines the effect of changing one or more factors of the portfolio (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, check Investment choices in Section 8.1.2.3, Pg# 127)
Note: For exam, know the definition of all 6 Investment Choices as mentioned in Standard 3rd ed
- Budget Variability determines the effect of changing the portfolio
- Market-payoff variability focuses on pricing and sales forecasts and depends on a number of marketing factors
- Performance variability analyzes the performance of the portfolio

questions.text: There has been recent major developments in the top management of Hazara Enterprises Ltd. The CEO has just been stepped down, and a new one is joining from the next week. Organizational announcement has been made. What will the portfolio manager do as the first step?

options.text: Meet with the new CEO and introduce yourself
Do nothing. This is beyond your scope of engagement
Meet with the PGB to discuss the issue of potential impact
Document your concerns in the portfolio risk register

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation The first step that Portfolio Manager would take is to document the situation as a potential risk in the Risk Register (Refer Risk Register in Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 130,131)
- There is no mention of an issue situation in this scenario, and if there is any, this discussion is going to be at later step
- Meeting with the new CEO can be an option for later step
- Do Nothing is not a choice for Portfolio Manager in almost all of the scenarios except if it is for regulatory or governmental requirements which is outside the authority of Portfolio Manager

questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager of the City Renovation portfolio in Bin Laden organization. You are currently working on developing the portfolio strategy with Portfolio Sponsor. Which technique is used to identify gaps in focus, investment or alignment within a portfolio?
questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
The process being discussed here is ‘Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan’. Strategic Alignment Analysis is a T&T of this process. Strategic Alignment Analysis focuses on the new or changing organizational strategy and objectives. The analysis also indicates where there are gaps in focus, investment, or alignment within the portfolio (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 3.1.1 Pg# 31)

- Gap Analysis is a T&T of Manage Strategic Change process. It is performed to compare the current portfolio mix and components with the new strategic direction and the “to-be” organizational vision

- Scenario Analysis is a T&T of Develop Portfolio Charter process. It enables decision makers to create a variety of portfolio scenarios using different combinations of both potential and current components, evaluating their possible outcomes

- Capability and Capacity Analysis is a T&T of Develop Portfolio Charter process. It is performed to understand how much work portfolio is able to perform based on the resources available (capacity), as well as their specific skillset (capability)

questions.text: You are working as Portfolio Manager in the ERP portfolio of Al-Hamd organization. A Consultant assigned to one of the critical project in your portfolio is going on vacation for 1 month. This may have a potential impact on your portfolio. What will you do as Portfolio Manager?

options.text: Hire another SME from the portfolio budget
Do interdependency analysis and assess the impact
Do Nothing. This is Project related concern and Project Manager will take care of it

questions.explanation:
Portfolio Manager will perform interdependency analysis and impact assessment of the risk that is about to trigger to come up with a contingency plan for 1 month
- Do Nothing is not a choice here. The absence of Consultant may have an impact on the project and overall portfolio objectives as project is of critical nature. Portfolio Manager needs to take the ownership of issue
- Hiring of another SME is not a viable option as the hiring process may take time, may be costly too
- Informing all other components manager is not going to solve the concern

questions.text: Due to unstable petroleum market prices, the management of your organization has decided to sell off all petroleum production assets and will now focus on the Gasoline production. To achieve this objective, the company acquired XYZ Gasoline Inc. Which portfolio management process is involved here?
questions.explanation:
'Manage Strategic Change' process enables to manage the changes in organizational strategy and to enhance the ability to accept and act on significant strategic changes that impact portfolio planning and management (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 52)
- 'Optimise Portfolio' process optimizes and balances the portfolio for performance and value delivery
- 'Define Portfolio' process deals with the identification, categorization and evaluation of portfolio components
- 'Define Portfolio Strategic Plan' process deals with defining the vision, objectives and strategy of portfolio

questions.text: CEO of your organization ABC Tech, Mr. Abbas Sheikh, informed you via email to add a new Mobile application initiative to your IT portfolio. What will be your action step as a Portfolio Manager?

options.text: Request the CEO to provide you with a written approval
Evaluate component proposal and present it to next PGB meeting

questions.explanation:
As per the role of Portfolio Manager, he evaluates and guides component selection, prioritization, balancing and termination. The final decision regarding component selection will be taken by PGB (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 1.8, 5.4 Pg# 14, 77-78)

- Portfolio Manager can't just proceed with component initiation without taking PGB approval. Though CEO may already be part of PGB, but approval from whole PGB committee is required for component selection and initiation
- CEO may already be part of PGB, however, the component authorization (Initiation, Termination, Change approval) is responsibility of governance board, and cant be taken solely by CEO
- Portfolio Manager cannot just reject the proposal. He will evaluate the request and present the assessment results to PGB. The component approval or rejection decision making authority lies with PGB

questions.text: Portfolio Evaluation (Prioritization) models include Scoring models or Ranking models, such as Multi-Criteria Scoring and Multi-Criteria Weighted Ranking models. These models include certain criteria used in the evaluation process to select initiatives base on the strategic fit. Which of the below is considered as criteria used in the component evaluation process?

options.text: Market Share, Benefits (financial & non-financial), Goals and Objectives
Market Share, ROI, Goals and Objectives, Type of Portfolio components
Urgency, Strategic Alignment, Dependency, Qualitative benefits

questions.explanation:
Market Share, Benefits and Goals & Objectives are portfolio component Evaluation criteria
Note: It is very important to know the portfolio component Identification, Categorization and Evaluation criteria for exam, as per the PMI Standard (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 66,67 for exhaustive list of component Evaluation Criteria)
- other choices have few component identification and categorization criterion as well

questions.text: You are managing the portfolio level risks in a document called Risk Register. The identified risk "Disruption to cement material supply due to dollar rate increase" under the marketplace EEF risk category has occurred. How will you communicate this issue to the portfolio wide stakeholders, according to the communication matrix?
questions.explanation:
The best way to communicate issue related information to wide portfolio audience is via Portfolio Issue Reports. Had the question asked about communicating issue information to key/specific portfolio stakeholders then Portfolio Issue Register would have been the correct choice.

- Issue Register may have some additional (may be confidential e.g. contingency reserves,management reserves etc) information that not wide portfolio stakeholders would be interested in knowing
- Though the issue is already part of Risk Register, however, when risk has become an issue then the better way to communicate the information to portfolio wide SH is via Portfolio Issue Reports

questions.text: In a Performance Review meeting of Design portfolio, you as the Portfolio Manager is visually presenting the progress and status of portfolio to the PGB representatives via a tool. What is the name of the tool along with its description?

options.text: Dashboard, A graphical display to communicate multiple messages on portfolio status and trends simultaneously
Performance Report, A graphical display to communicate multiple messages on portfolio status and trends simultaneously
Communication Matrix, A tool used to communicate information to the portfolio stakeholders and the planned frequency
Dashboard, A tool used to communicate information to the portfolio stakeholders and the planned frequency

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Dashboards are visual representation to communicate multiple messages on portfolio status and trending simultaneously. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.2.2.4, Pg# 117)
- Communication Matrix is a planning tool to record portfolio communication format, mode and frequency
- Performance reports are not visual representation of portfolio progress
- Communication Matrix is a planning tool to record portfolio communication format, mode and frequency

questions.text: You are working as Portfolio Manager for Social Development portfolio in Sindh province. The portfolio is progressing as expected and PGB is overall satisfied with the portfolio value generation in the form of increased employment rate, literacy rate and no of hospitals in the region over the past year. How do you perform risk management at the portfolio level?

options.text: Accept risk within organization risk tolerance

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Portfolio Manager accepts risks within organization risk tolerance (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 120)
- At portfolio level, Portfolio Manager does not minimize negative risk or maximize positive risk, rather he works to maximize portfolio value within organization risk tolerance
- Black Swans are risks with low probability and very high impact e.g. Covid, Earthquakes, Storms, Tsunami etc. Portfolio Manage work to manage all portfolio risks within organizational risk tolerance

questions.text: Mr. Ahmed is the portfolio manager for KSFH, a leading bank of Pakistan. He generated inventory of work from components in the enterprise. What is the output of this process?
questions.explanation: During 'Define Strategic Plan' process, Portfolio Manager applies Inventory of Work to Portfolio Component Inventory to come up with an initial list of Portfolio. Portfolio may further evolve in the later processes of Portfolio Management to reduce gaps to meet strategic objectives (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.1.1.2, 4.1.2.1, 4.1.3.2 Pg# 43, 44, 46) PSP is another output of 'Develop Strategic Plan' but does not fit this scenario, PR is developed at later stages, Portfolio structure is developed as part of PC which is developed at later stages

questions.text: Two portfolios ABC and MNO have investments of 5M PKR and 25M PKR respectively. On the Efficient Frontier, where is Portfolio ABC located with respect to Portfolio MNO?

options.text: On the high part of the curve to the right
On the lower part of the curve to the left

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Portfolio ABC would be on low part of the curve to the left

- A portfolio aims to be on the curve to be efficient
- A portfolio on the Efficient Frontier is never above the curve
- Portfolio MNO would be on high part of the curve to the right

questions.text: You have observed that the documents/templates across the components are inconsistent, and components in your portfolio generate inconsistent reports as well. There are standards defined in your portfolio. What will you do as a Portfolio Manager?

options.text: Establish and maintain needed templates and procedures
Develop and maintain needed templates and procedures
Consult PMO. PMO is responsible to establish and maintain needed templates and procedures
Consult PMO. PMO is responsible to develop and maintain needed templates and procedures

questions.explanation: PMO is responsible for developing and maintaining standards, while Portfolio Manager is responsible for establishing (implementing) and maintaining standards. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 14,17)

questions.text: During the execution of your portfolio, you have noticed that one of your components should be terminated. There is enough funds remaining after the termination of this project. Other portfolio components are in need of financial resources. What Portfolio Management processes you are involved in?
questions.explanation:
In ‘Optimize Portfolio’, Portfolio Manager determines resource C&C, prioritization and the portfolio components to be suspended, reprioritized, or terminated based on the balancing or rebalancing activities. In ‘Authorize Portfolio’, Portfolio Manager presents the findings of ‘Optimize Portfolio’ to PGB in portfolio review meetings. PGB makes decision of reallocation of funding and resources from deactivated and terminated portfolio components to the activated portfolio components or send them back to the organization resource pool (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 77,77,78)
- In ‘Define portfolio’, an up-to-date list of qualified portfolio components by identifying, categorizing, scoring, and ranking portfolio components
- In ‘Provide portfolio Oversight’, PGB monitor the portfolio to ensure alignment with the organizational strategy and objectives and make governance decisions

questions.text: Your organization Rabbi Constructions is experiencing an increased competition in the Construction industry of KSA. The organization has now decided to focus on the use of innovative technology. To achieve this objective, the company has acquired Al-Rehman Enterprises. As the Portfolio Manager of Rabbi Constructions, what will be your best course of action?

options.text: Do nothing, as nothing has really changed for Rabbi Constructions
Inform all stakeholders and update the Strategic Plan
Balance the existing mix of portfolio components

questions.explanation: Overall explanation Stakeholder Analysis is a T&T for Manage Strategic Change process. It helps to ensure continuity and align key stakeholders' expectations with the changing strategy and resulting portfolio realignment (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 54) - Strategic Plan gets updated as part of Manage Strategic Change. However, at this stage all portfolio stakeholders will not be informed of this major strategic change - This is a major strategic change for Rabbi Constructions. Portfolio Manager needs to perform his role in that - Once the changes in Strategic Management processes are done due to this change, then the component balancing part would come

questions.text: One of the key stakeholder Ms. Rana Ahsan in your Confectionery & Bakers portfolio got a promotion and became Sales Director. He became less interested in your portfolio and you used to engage him very closely. What is your best course of action in this case?

options.text: Meet with the stakeholder and analyze his requirements again
This is a usual situation, you should continue work as normal
Escalate the issue to the PGB in order to solve the issue from a management perspective

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
In this case, Portfolio Manager can directly change key stakeholder grouping to third quadrant (high influence, low interest) from fourth quadrant (high influence, high interest) in the stakeholder communication strategy matrix (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.1.2.3, Pg# 112)
- The fact that the stakeholder lost his interest in the portfolio means that he has been already analyzed
- Escalating the issue is out of question and does not reflect the correct responsibilities of a portfolio manager.
- The portfolio manager should act upon such a change and should not continue work as normal

questions.text: The Portfolio Management Information System (PMIS) enables the Portfolio Manager to define, analyze, design, produce, and manage systems to support a successful portfolio. PMIS is a collection of manual (i.e. spreadsheets) and automated tools. Which of the following is an attribute of a PMIS?
questions.explanation: PMIS is neither used as a training and learning hub, nor as a recording system for stakeholder opinion. One of its uses is to archive data for future use; which in our case is the option related to archiving legal data (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 2.4, Pg# 25)

questions.text: Which of the following is an example of Portfolio Process Asset?

options.text: Performance Measurement Databases, Templates & Portfolio reports

questions.explanation:
PPAs include formal and informal plans, policies, templates, procedures, and guidelines. The process assets also include the portfolio related knowledge bases, such as lessons learned and historical information. Portfolio process assets may include information on tools, techniques, models, integrated schedules, and risk and performance data (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 37 for more PPA examples)
- Stakeholder Risk Tolerance and Portfolio Management Information System (PMIS) are examples EEFs
- Organisation Risk Tolerance is an example of OPA

questions.text: CEO has requested that Portfolio Manager calculate the health of the portfolio to achieve the benefits to the organization. The organization has placed more importance on the CPI metric than the SPI metric, weighing cost at 80% and schedule at 20%. What is the Composite Index of the portfolio?
questions.explanation:
A ratio of 1.0 suggests that work is progressing as planned and expected. A ratio of >1.0 suggests that work is progressing as planned, but outside the usual range (i.e. 1.0). A ratio <1.0 suggests that work is not progressing as planned (i.e. 1.0)

Portfolio Composite Index (CI) / Critical Ratio (CR) = Sum [(NPV / Sum(NPVs)) * ((CPI * weight) + (SPI * weight))]. CPI & SPI weights are 80% and 20% respectively.
when NPV is not present in the calculation, then Portfolio CI = Avg [(CPI * weight) + (SPI * weight)]

Detailed Calculation is present in the above table. Composite Index of given portfolio is 1.01
Note: This is a very important and tricky questions for the exam. Do practice it before sitting in the real exam

questions.text: As the Portfolio Manager, you have scored the portfolio components and are analyzing the data in order to prioritize the components. Using the following multi-criteria scoring table, which of the options represents the correct component priority?
questions.explanation:
As per the above Multi-criteria scoring technique, the higher the component score, the higher the priority. Accordingly, the correct component priority is D-B-E-C-A.

Explanation Table:
Component A: Growth Value 50, Weight (%) 50, Score 25 | Additional Revenue Value 10, Weight (%) 75, Score 7.5 | Risk Reduction Value 90, Weight (%) 75, Score 67.5 | Component Score 100 | Priority 4
Component B: Growth Value 210, Weight (%) 150, Score 315 | Additional Revenue Value 16, Weight (%) 200, Score 32.0 | Risk Reduction Value 80, Weight (%) 50, Score 40 | Component Score 387.6 | Priority 2
Component C: Growth Value 120, Weight (%) 75, Score 90 | Additional Revenue Value 22, Weight (%) 120, Score 26.4 | Risk Reduction Value 150, Weight (%) 150, Score 225 | Component Score 341.4 | Priority 3
Component D: Growth Value 250, Weight (%) 75, Score 187.5 | Additional Revenue Value 24, Weight (%) 120, Score 28.8 | Risk Reduction Value 230, Weight (%) 150, Score 345 | Component Score 661.3 | Priority 1
Component E: Growth Value 180, Weight (%) 150, Score 270 | Additional Revenue Value 17, Weight (%) 250, Score 42.5 | Risk Reduction Value 150, Weight (%) 50, Score 75 | Component Score 387.6 | Priority 2

Based on component scores:
D (661.3) > B (387.6) = E (387.6) > C (341.4) > A (100.0)
Thus, the priority order is D-B-E-C-A.

questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager of the City Renovation portfolio in Bin Laden organization. You are currently working on developing the portfolio strategy with Portfolio Sponsor. Which document aligns the Portfolio to the Organizational Strategic plan and objectives?
questions.explanation:
Portfolio Strategic Plan has Vision, Goals and Objectives as its contents, that aligns the portfolio to the organizational strategy and objectives (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.1.3.1, Pg# 46)

- Portfolio Roadmap is a high level chronological representation of portfolio components, along with milestones, key dependencies and deliverables. It defines the direction of portfolio
- Portfolio Charter defines the portfolio structure and formally authorizes the portfolio manager in the portfolio
- Portfolio Management plan defines how the portfolio will be planned and managed

questions.text: As the Portfolio Manager of Al-Jazeerah Incorporations, you are working to establish how the organizational strategy and objectives will be implemented in a portfolio. Which of the following process groups are you involved in?
questions.explanation:
Defining process group deals with establishment of organizational strategy through plans and vision in portfolio (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 3.11 Pg# 31)

- Aligning Process Group consists of processes to manage and optimize the portfolio. This group determines how portfolio components will be categorized, evaluated, selected for inclusion, modification, or elimination, and managed in the portfolio.
- Authorizing and Controlling Process Group consists of the Governance processes for determining how to authorize the portfolio and provides ongoing portfolio oversight

questions.text: The CEO of your organization has requested you to provide the probability of your portfolio achieving a NPV of $50M - $100m along with the corresponding confidence levels. You will perform which of the following analysis technique?

options.text: Monte Carlo Analysis and present cumulative frequency distribution curve

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
In Monte Carlo simulation, the model is iterated many times. At each iteration, the input values (such as cost of project elements or duration of schedule activities or NPV, IRR etc) are randomized in accordance with the probability distribution of the corresponding variable. The outputs of each iteration are consolidated to provide a frequency distribution for the probability values of each key parameter (such as total cost or completion date). Keyword for Cumulative Frequency distribution is "Probability" (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 128 for Cumulative Frequency s-curve, and Pg# 133 for Monte Carlo Analysis)
- Sensitivity analysis helps to determine which risks have the most potential impact/variability on the portfolio. Tornado diagram displays the contribution of the identified risks to the value of one strategic objective (NPV in this case)
- SWOT Analysis is a qualitative technique to determine portfolio strengths, weaknesses, opportunities and strengths
- What-if analysis is a type of Scenario analysis that enables decision makers to create a variety of portfolio scenarios using different combinations of potential and current portfolio components and evaluating their possible outcomes based on various assumptions.

questions.text: Your CEO asked you to calculate the overall performance of your Portfolio XYZ with the below data. The company CPI and SPI tolerance is +/- 2% (Healthy Range)
questions.explanation: Overall explanation NPV in the question is considered as weights. We will calculate Portfolio XYZ CPI and SPI by taking weighted average of component CPI and SPI a) Portfolio XYZ CPI = [(1.3*3)+(0.95*2)+(1.0*1.5)+(1.0*12)+(0.9*6)] / (3+2+1.5+12+6) = 1.008 b) Portfolio XYZ SPI = [(1.2*3)+(1.3*2)+(0.9*1.5)+(1.0*12)+(0.8*6)] / (3+2+1.5+12+6) = 0.994

questions.text: You are the Portfolio Manager of Borjan Inc. While optimizing your portfolio, you need to present to the PGB how your components will be ranked and balanced in a quantifiable way. What tool and technique will you use?
questions.explanation:
Weighted Ranking and Scoring are the techniques for evaluating and ranking portfolio components based on predefined criteria (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 74)
- Graphical Analytical tools are not a T&T for prioritization and ranking of portfolio components
- C&C mgmt deals with the portfolio resource management and constraints. It is not a T&T for prioritization and ranking of portfolio components
- Scenario Analysis is an analytical method that enables decision makers to create a variety of portfolio scenarios using different combinations of both potential portfolio and current components and evaluating their possible outcomes based on various assumptions. It is not a T&T for prioritization and ranking of portfolio components

options.text: Increased Profitability, Market Share Increase, Process Improvement, Continuous Improvement
Revenue Increase, Cost Reduction, Market Share Increase, Risks
Risks, Business Imperative, Regulatory, Goals and Objectives

questions.text: Portfolio Management Plan documents the roles and responsibilities across the portfolio. Which of the following is true in this regard?

options.text: The roles and responsibilities portfolio is determined during the Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan process
Portfolio Organization Structure Analysis is created using the technique called Portfolio Management Organization Structure
Portfolio Management Organization Structure is created using the technique called Portfolio organization structure analysis
Portfolio Management Organization Structure is created using Scenario Analysis

questions.explanation: Portfolio Roles and Responsibilities are created during the process 'Develop Portfolio Management plan'. PMOS is part of Governance Model in Portfolio Management plan. In this process, the portfolio manager assigns reporting roles and responsibilities across each program, project, or operational component (PMOS) using POSA technique (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 5.1.2.2, Pg# 61)

questions.text: You are the Portfolio Manager for the IT Management Portfolio in the Standard Bank of Pakistan. You have observed that 10 key stakeholders from relevant ministries are not attending meeting. There are 67 key stakeholders on the portfolio. What will you do as the Portfolio Manager?

options.text: Discuss the issue with all 67 key stakeholders openly and highlight the importance of attending Portfolio meetings
Discuss the issue with the 10 stakeholders separately and highlight importance of attending Portfolio meetings
Discuss the issue with the 10 stakeholders in a joint meeting and highlight importance of attending Portfolio meetings

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
The best choice here is that Portfolio Manager explains the importance of attending meetings to all stakeholders, so that no-one thinks about missing them in the future

- Escalation is an extreme step and should be the last resort. Portfolio Manager would resolve the issue at his end
- Portfolio Manager would not want to embarrass anyone
c) Discuss the issue with the 10 stakeholders separately is going to be very hectic for Portfolio Manager

questions.text: One of your component managers came to you to tell you about a risk affecting his component that will badly impact the component and might affect the portfolio. After assessment, the risk turned out to be of low probability with high impact. What do you do as a portfolio manager?

options.text: Inform the component manager to add the risk to the risk register and follow up on it closely
Inform him to submit a change request to raise the component contingency because of this risk
Inform the component manager to add the risk to the risk register, assign a senior risk owner to it in order to follow up on it closely
Inform him that he does not need to worry, you will have a risk contingency reserve for his risk at a portfolio level

questions.explanation: Low probability and high impact risks are mitigated by means of contingency reserves at the portfolio level, called equity protection.(Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Portfolio Risk Management, Pg# 120)

questions.text: Imad Ali is part of JellyBeans Confectioneries, and has recently been promoted to PMO Director. With the change in role, his level of interest and influence in Freshmint Gums portfolio has been changed. As the Portfolio Manager of Freshmint Gums portfolio, what will be your best course of action?

options.text: Do Nothing. Change in Interest and Influence does not change anything

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Level of Influence and Interest is part of Stakeholder Communication Strategy Matrix (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.1.2.1, Fig 7-5, Pg# 111)

- Portfolio Manager needs to take ownership of the situation. Do nothing is not a choice here
- Level of Influence and Interest does not get updated in Communication Matrix
- Update the Communication Management Plan may be a choice, as CMP eventually gets updated as a result of change in influence and interest, however, option b) is the best choice here

questions.text: Western Power, a leading Energy company in Africa has recently acquired United Powers company in Africa. The CEO of Western Power has asked you in your position as the Portfolio Manager of Western Power portfolio, to determine if components of United Powers should be continued or not? What will be your best course of action?

options.text: Compare United Powers portfolio with the organization objectives of Western Power
Compare components of Western Power portfolio with that of United Powers portfolio
Compare Western Power portfolio with United Powers portfolio
Compare performance metrics of Western Power and United Powers portfolios

questions.explanation: Performance Metrics monitor strategic goal achievement, financial contribution, stakeholder satisfaction, risk profile, and resource utilization. Performance Metrics measure quantitative or qualitative information aggregated from the portfolio components (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 89)

questions.text: Which of the following criteria belongs to Prioritization? (select all correct choices)
questions.explanation: Prioritization criteria here refers to the Evaluation criteria (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 66,67 for more Evaluation/Prioritization criteria) Note: Knowledge of Key Descriptors, Categorization and Evaluation criteria as mentioned in Standard 3rd ed are very important from the exam perspective

questions.text: DSL academy is a portfolio of DSL Group. An identified risk has occurred on the DSL academy portfolio. As the Portfolio Manager of DSL academy, you need to determine the accountability for this risk. Which of the below document will you assess?
questions.explanation:
Risk Register content contains Risk Category, Risk Statement, Ownership, Probability, Impact, Risk Score, Frequency, Trigger, Response Strategy, Response Plan, Contingency etc. (Refer Risk Register in Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 180,181)
- PSP does not contain risk ownership
- PMP contains Risk Management plan (risk strategy and methodology), but does not contain risk ownership
- RMP contains risk strategy and methodology, but does not contain risk ownership

questions.text: You are newly appointed as the Portfolio Manager of the The Holy Haram Extension and Renovation portfolio in Al-I landasah organization. Recently, an approval was granted by PGB for the inclusion of renovation of Mataf area project into your portfolio. You were part of the meeting. What will you do right after the meeting?

options.text: Record Meeting minutes and update the decision in governance decision report
Communication to all stakeholders as per Communication Management Plan

questions.explanation:
The first thing Portfolio Manager would do is to update the governance decision and record meeting minutes
- Communication to all stakeholders as per Communication Management Plan will be done, but not as a first step
- Governance decisions do not get circulated to all portfolio stakeholders equally, rather only the intended recipients receive it as per the Communication Matrix
- Proceeding with project execution will be done later in portfolio management but not as the first step

questions.text: Portfolio Sponsor is part of the Portfolio Governance Board(PGB) and is responsible for providing funding and ensuring the strategic alignment. PGB has decision making rights, provides oversight to the portfolio and is also responsible for resource allocation/reallocation approvals. PGB decisions are recorded in:
questions.explanation:
As part of Portfolio Oversight process, governance decisions are made and they are recorded in Governance Decision reports which is part of Portfolio Reports (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 3.2.1.2 Pg# 37)
- Portfolio Management Plan defines how the Portfolio oversight would take, but it does not record the governance decisions
- PPAs may include Portfolio Reports, however, the better and more specific answer here is Portfolio Reports
- OPAs do not include any document/deliverable specific to portfolio

questions.text: Use the Single Criterion prioritization model to tell the order of priority for the 6 projects listed below (A-F):
questions.explanation:
Overall explanation A,F,C,B,D,E.

Portfolio further evolves in the later processes of Portfolio Management to reduce gaps to meet strategic objectives (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.1.2, 4.1.2.1, 4.1.3.2 Pg# 43, 44, 46) PCI is the tool and Portfolio is the output (order matters), POSA and PC is the wrong O/P in this scenario

questions.text: The role of the Portfolio Manager includes which of the following?

options.text: Develop and maintain the needed templates and procedures
Responsible to provide funding to portfolio components
Guiding the selection and prioritization of initiatives

questions.explanation:
Portfolio Manager guides the selection, prioritization, balancing, and termination of portfolio components to ensure the alignment with strategic goals and organizational priorities; (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 14)
- Responsible to provide funding to portfolio components is the responsibility of Portfolio Sponsor
- Development and maintenance of the needed templates and procedures is the responsibility of PMO
- Allocation/Reallocation of resources to components is the responsibility of Portfolio governance board

questions.text: You have observed that the documents/templates across the components are not standardized, and components in your portfolio generate inconsistent reports as well. What will you do as a Portfolio Manager?

options.text: Consult PMO. PMO is responsible to develop and maintain needed templates and procedures
Develop and maintain needed templates and procedures
Consult PMO. PMO is responsible to establish and maintain needed templates and procedures

questions.explanation:
PMO is responsible for developing and maintaining standards and the Portfolio Manager is responsible for establishing (implementing) and maintaining standards. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 14,17)
- PMIS is not used for documentation, report and template standardization
- The other options are not correct R&R for Portfolio Manager

questions.text:
Consider the 3 projects X, Y, Z in your portfolio ABC. Answer the following:
- What is the component score for project Y?
- If you have the budget to execute only one project in your portfolio, which among X, Y, Z projects will you select?
questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
[Table showing Project, Criteria 1 (Revenue Generation), Rank 1, Criteria 2 (Market Share), Rank 2, Criteria 3 (ROI), Rank 3, Project Score (Simple Average of ranks of all criteria), Priority]
Project X: $3M, 3, 30%, 2, 40%, 3, (3+2+3)/3 = 2.667, 3
Project Y: $5M, 1, 20%, 3, 60%, 2, (1+3+2)/3 = 2, 2

a) Project Y score = 2
b) In Multi-criteria Weighted Ranking model, the lower the component score, the highest the priority i.e. Component Priority: Z, Y, X. Accordingly, if Portfolio Manager has to select one project in the portfolio, it would be project Z

questions.text: Company ABC fertilizers acquired Company XYZ chemicals to enter the chemical market. This is a result of change in Company ABC fertilizers organizational strategic objectives. What documents needs to be changed to reflect the new portfolio vision?
questions.explanation: Portfolio Strategic Plan has Portfolio Vision and Objectives as one of its contents (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.1.3.1, Pg# 46) PR, PMP, PC do not contain Vision

questions.text: Which of the following is not part of Portfolio Performance Management domain?
questions.explanation: Portfolio Prioritization is performed as part of Strategic and Governance Management domains, rest of the choices are part of Portfolio Performance Management domain

questions.text: You are managing a portfolio in a functional organization and resources are shared between operations and projects. You are continuously performing capability and capacity analysis in order to optimize the portfolio. Which of the following capability and capacity analysis is used to limit the number or size of components the organization can execute?
questions.explanation:
Financial resource capability and capacity is the constraining factors for the number of portfolio components OR the size of portfolio components the organization can execute (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 6.3.2.1, Pg# 74)
- Human resource capability and capacity is the limiting factors for the number of portfolio components the organization can execute
- Asset capacity is a limiting factor for the number of portfolio components AND the size of portfolio components the organization can execute

questions.text: Portfolio Management Plan documents the roles and responsibilities across the portfolio. Which of the following is true in this regard?

options.text: The roles and responsibilities portfolio is determined during the Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan process
Portfolio Management Organization Structure is created using Scenario Analysis
Portfolio Organization Structure Analysis is created using the technique called Portfolio Management Organization Structure
Portfolio Management Organization Structure is created using the technique called Portfolio organization structure analysis

questions.explanation: Portfolio Roles and Responsibilities are created during the process 'Develop Portfolio Management plan'. In this process, the portfolio manager assigns reporting roles and responsibilities across each program, project, or operational component (PMOS) using POSA technique (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 5.1.2.2, Pg# 61)

questions.text: An event is identified which can have a huge positive impact on the portfolio. What will the portfolio manager do first?

options.text: Bring to the attention of the Portfolio Governance Board
Bring to the attention of the Portfolio Sponsor
Commence process to enhance this opportunity

questions.explanation: After risk identification (both threats and opportunities), the very first thing that needs to be done is to document it into Risk Register. Risk Assessment, Response Planning and Monitoring is a later step. Note: When risk is urgent, then a preliminary probability / impact assessment and a response is required to be documented along with the risk in Risk Register - After Identification, first the opportunity (positive risk) needs to be documented in risk registered, assessed and then response plan will be created to decide if it is going to enhanced/exploited/escalated/shared/accepted - if opportunity is going to be beyond acceptable threshold of portfolio, only then it needs to be ESCALATED (discussed with Sponsor or PGB or Organizational Management), else it will be taken by Portfolio Manager and portfolio team

questions.text: As the Portfolio Manager, one of your responsibility includes guiding the evaluation and selection of initiatives. When are the components evaluated on a portfolio?
questions.explanation: Portfolio components are identified, categorized, evaluated and prioritized during the Defining process group. They keep on reevaluated, reprioritized and balanced by Portfolio Manager and the team throughout the Aligning process group. The decision making and authorization based on re-evaluation is done by PGB in the phase gate reviews during the Authorizing and Controlling process group (Hint: I->C->E->S->P->B i.e. Identify->Categorize->Evaluate->Prioritize->Balance)

questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager of the City Renovation portfolio in Bin Laden organization. You are currently working on developing the portfolio strategy with Portfolio Sponsor. Which T&T outputs the initial high level version of portfolio and what is the process involved?

options.text: Strategic Alignment Analysis, Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan
Portfolio Component Inventory, Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan

questions.explanation:
During 'Develop Strategic Plan' process, Portfolio Manager applies Inventory of Work as a starting point to Portfolio Component Inventory tool to come up with an initial list of Portfolio. Portfolio further evolves in the later processes of Portfolio Management (i.e. Define Portfolio) to reduce gaps to meet strategic objectives (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.1.1.2, 4.1.2.1, 4.1.3.2 Pg# 43, 44, 46)
- Define Portfolio process produces the full-fledged list of portfolio components
- Prioritization Analysis defines the priorities and order of portfolio components in the Roadmap
- Strategic Alignment Analysis focuses on where are gaps in focus, investment, or organizational alignment within the portfolio, and reflects that in Strategic Plan

questions.text: Ms. Hina Qaiser, the CIO of your organization has raised a concern that the portfolio performance reports received by her are inconsistent and inaccurate. As the Portfolio Manager, what will be your course of action?

options.text: Meet with CIO to discuss her communication needs
Update the SH Communication Strategy Matrix

questions.explanation:
Communication Req Analysis will be reviewed to check if meaningful info has been extracted from raw communication data to present to key SHs. One way to help make data meaningful is to build forecasts based on trends in the data. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.2.2.3, Pg# 117)
- updating CMP comes after reviewing Communication Req analysis
- the scenario does not depict a problem with SH needs, it is correctly stated in SH Matrix/Register
- Communication Strategy Matrix update does not make sense here as SH needs have not really changed

questions.text: Due to multiple issues, there were changes in the reporting process in your portfolio; the meetings with their frequencies have been changed and this will also affect the reporting cycle times. In order to meet this new change you will update which of the following documents?
questions.explanation:
Communication Calendar is a representation of all of the communication for the portfolio and their frequency over a period of time. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.2.2.4, Pg# 117)

- PMIS and Communication Strategy Matrix do not tell about communication frequencies
- the decision may impact communication frequency in Communication Matrix, however the eventual change will be implemented in Communication Calendar

questions.text: Due to multiple issues, there were changes in the reporting process in your portfolio; the meetings with their frequencies have been changed and this will also affect the reporting cycle times. In order to meet this new change you will update which of the following documents?
questions.explanation: Overall explanation: Communication Calendar is a representation of all of the communication for the portfolio and their frequency over a period of time. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.2.2.4, Pg# 117) - PMIS and Communication Strategy Matrix do not tell about communication frequencies - the decision may impact communication frequency in Communication Matrix, however the eventual change will be implemented in Communication Calendar

questions.text: As part of the periodical strategic management cycle, the portfolio management team is revising the portfolio and re-doing the strategic management part. Currently, they are assuming and evaluating different combinations of components in order to come up with multiple approaches and take a decision on the portfolio structure. What is currently being performed?
questions.explanation: Portfolio Structure is developed as part of the 'Develop Portfolio Charter' process, and the analysis that we are doing here is the Scenario Analysis, which is aimed to determine the various combinations of portfolio components to come up with portfolio structure for inclusion in the Portfolio Charter (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 4.2.2.1, Pg# 48) - 'Readiness Assessment' and 'Stakeholder Analysis' are T&Ts of Manage Strategic change process, which is not the case in the question scenario - Though 'Capability and Capacity Analysis' is performed as part of 'Develop Portfolio Charter' process, however, the scenario in the question is not talking about the amount of work to be performed in the portfolio based on resources availability or their skillset

questions.text: There was a change in your portfolio and the senior management has informed you that this change will not impact any process in the portfolio. However, the organization risk tolerance will be impacted. What will you do as a Portfolio Manager?

options.text: You will update the Strategic Plan to reflect the new risk tolerance
You will refer to the "change management and control" section of the portfolio management plan for guidance
You will request a meeting with governance to assess the impact of this change
You will revise the roadmap and rebalance resources

questions.explanation: Risk tolerance is one of the contents of Portfolio Strategic plan. Accordingly, it will be updated in this case. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 4.1.3.1, Pg# 46)

questions.text: The below 3 initiatives are under evaluation in the Bakery portfolio of Al-Hilal Foods and Confectioneries: From the given information, please provide the order of prioritization?
questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Expected Monetary Value (EMV) = Probability X Impact (NPV)
EMV (Project X): (0.2 x 300) = 60
EMV (Program Y): (0.4 x 200) = 80
EMV (Program Z): (1.0 x 90) = 90
The highest the EMV, the highest the priority i.e. order of initiative prioritization is Z, Y, X

Note: '# of product to market by Dec, 2022' factor in the provided data does not have any contribution in the calculation of initiative prioritization, and is a total distractor here

questions.text: Your portfolio has a mature portfolio management framework and methodology. Who guides the portfolio team to follow processes, procedures and metrics?
questions.explanation:
Portfolio Manager establishes (implement) and maintains portfolio framework, methodology and processes (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 1.8 Pg# 14)
Note: Read carefully to the roles and responsibilities of PMO and Portfolio Manager for exam
- Portfolio Sponsor is responsible for funding, organizational resource provision and portfolio scope
- PMO establishes standardization, develops and maintain portfolio framework and processes
- PGB roles and responsibilities include component authorization, portfolio oversight, decision making, prioritization and portfolio performance review wrt organizational objectives

questions.text: The CEO of Al Khalij Materials has announced a new organizational strategic move to capture 60% market share of the construction raw materials sales in MENA region. The organization now plans to build cement plants in Bahrain, Qatar, Kuwait and Abu Dhabi. Previously, the organization had only 1 cement plant in KSA. The strategic objective to capture 60% market share in MENA is considered a very aggressive target. Which management style is best suited for Al Khalij Materials?
questions.explanation: Directing: This management style assists in providing direction and vision to employees towards the accomplishment of strategic objectives

questions.text: The CEO of Almirah Gas Pvt Ltd had defined the organizational goals and objectives in annual strategic planning exercise. This will be an input to which portfolio management process?
questions.explanation:
Organizational strategy and objectives is an input to the Develop Portfolio strategic Plan process. It provides long-term direction, vision, goals, and objectives, which becomes content of Strategic plan as the primary output of this process (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 4.1.1 Pg# 43)

- Portfolio Strategic Plan and Portfolio Management Plan are key deliverables, not processes
- Organizational strategy is not an input to Develop Portfolio Charter process

questions.text: During one of your meetings with the component managers in your portfolio, Mr Hassan, the Project Manager, informs you of a major issue involving contractor under performance on his project. What is the most likely next step?

options.text: Mr. Hassan should be updating Risk Register
Nothing is expected at project level. This situation will now be dealt at Portfolio Manager level
Mr. Hassan should be conducting Root Cause Analysis
Mr. Hassan should be updating Issue Register

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
After an issue is identified at project level, it will first be opened in Project Issue Register, will be assigned an owner and should be a regular topic of team status meetings until resolved
- today's issue may be a future risk on the project. Project Risk Register may also need to be updated once an issue is identified and assessed. However 'Updating Issue Register' is the best option
- RCA will definitely be done to come up with a proper cause, impact and corrective action of the issue, however, this will be done at a later step
- Issue is identified at project level, so it will first be root caused and corrected at that level, until Project Manager identifies that the issue is beyond project tolerance (or Project Manager authority level), and needs to be escalated to Program/Portfolio level for resolution.

questions.text: The government of your country has recently introduced some new regulatory changes. This enterprise environmental factor resulted in a major competitive disadvantage to your organization. This development has favoured your competitor and your company will now embark on a change in strategic direction and focus on new developments. As a Portfolio Manager, you want to earn the buy-in of your senior management in order to make this change successful. What is your course of action?
questions.explanation: This scenario describes 'Manage Strategic Change' process, which has Stakeholder Analysis technique. This analysis helps to ensure continuity and align key stakeholders' expectations with the changing strategy and resulting portfolio realignment. The techniques may include interviewing senior executive stakeholders to analyze expectations for strategic change. (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.4.2.1, Pg# 64) C&C is a T&T for Develop Portfolio Charter and SWOT Analysis is a T&T for Optimize Portfolio, which is not the case here. Readiness Assessment is a T&T for Manage Strategic Change, however, it is performed to assess how ready the organization is to perform the steps necessary to bridge the gap between the "as-is" portfolio and the "to-be" state. The scenario described here demands the use of Stakeholder Analysis technique to make strategic change

questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager in the ERP portfolio of Al-Hamd organization. You are currently in the aligning process group and measuring the portfolio benefits and value towards the organizational objectives. Cost vs Benefit analysis is a critical component of Business Case development. When is the Cost /Benefit analysis used in Portfolio Management?
questions.explanation: Throughout the portfolio lifecycle, Portfolio Manager ensures that portfolio is viable to execute, and benefits and value are delivered as per the alignment with organizational objectives. Cost/Benefits Analysis is a very useful technique to measure tangible portfolio benefits w.r.t portfolio investments - The other choices are incorrect. C/B Analysis happens throughout the portfolio lifecycle, not in just one process

questions.text: Which of the following T&T helps to prepare performance metrics?
questions.explanation:
Elicitation Technique is a T&T for Develop Portfolio Performance Management Plan process. In Elicitation, stakeholders and key subject matter experts are consulted during planning meetings, brainstorming sessions, interviews, or surveys to develop key performance measures (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 89)
- Stakeholder Analysis is not a T&T for Develop Portfolio Performance Management plan process
- PMIS is a tool for information collection and distribution to support the portfolio management processes. It does not use to develop performance metrics
- C&C is a technique performed to understand the human, financial, and asset C&C of the organization in order to select, fund, and execute portfolio components. It does not use to develop performance metrics

questions.text: Your organization Al-Fateh Enterprises is going through a major strategic change. This has resulted in the cancellation of few projects in your portfolio. As a Portfolio Manager, what will you do?

options.text: communicate the information to portfolio stakeholders
balance the existing mix of portfolio components

questions.explanation:
As few portfolio components are cancelled, Portfolio Manager needs to reevaluate, reprioritize and balance the current mix of portfolio components as part of Optimize Portfolio process
- communication of the information to portfolio stakeholders will be done at later stages
- there is no point to reevaluate the cancelled projects
- balancing will be done in this case, however, reprioritization with balancing is a better choice here

questions.text: Company ABC fertilizers acquired Company XYZ chemicals to enter the chemical market. This is a result of change in Company ABC fertilizers organizational strategic objectives. What document will reflect a change in the timeline of portfolio components?
questions.explanation:
Portfolio Roadmap contains the high level timeline (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.3.3.1, Pg# 81)
PMP, PSP and PC do not contain timeline

questions.text: What is Force Field?

options.text: an analytical tool to optimize portfolios given the resource constraints.
a tool that helps compare and balance portfolio components according to some pre-established portfolio component balancing criteria
an analysis to help determine which risks have the most impact on portfolio
a tool for root cause analysis that can help take action once the root cause has been identified

questions.explanation:
Force field analysis is a basic tool for root cause analysis that can help you take action once the root cause has been identified. The technique is based on the assumption that any situation is the result of forces for and against the current state being in equilibrium. Countering the opposing forces and/or increasing the favourable forces will help induce a change by reinforcing positives and eliminating or reducing negatives.

Force field analysis does the following:
- Presents the positives and negatives of a situation so they are easily comparable.
- Considers all aspects of making the desired change.

questions.text: During the optimization of ABC portfolio, you have noticed that one of your components is not performing up-to-the-mark and should be bring on track to remain aligned with strategic goals. Optimize Portfolio process balances trade-offs between? (select all correct choices)

options.text: Short term vs Long term goals

questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Portfolio optimization evaluates trade-offs of portfolio objectives, such as the management of risk and return, balancing short-term goals against long-term goals, and balancing project types to align with the organizational strategy and objectives (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 71)
Hint: ROI, NPV, Revenue etc. are considered as 'Return' on Portfolio Investment (i.e. Risk)

questions.text: Major organizational structural changes are now in place in Yokohama LLC following primary strategic changes. Your manager Mr. John Smith was promoted and is now VP Operations. With his new position, he has become less interested in your Software Development portfolio. You used to engage him closely previously. How will you manage Mr. John now?

Remove Mr. John from your Portfolio SH Register
Do Stakeholder Analysis to determine out Mr. John new communication requirement and interests
Nothing has really changed. Continue to engage Mr. John closely

- Mr. John is still a SH of Software Development portfolio
- Communication Requirement is not performed via SH Analysis technique
- Scenario clearly states that SH interest has changed, which requires change in communication strategy for Mr. John

You are currently working on developing the portfolio structure during Develop Portfolio Charter process. One of the secondary outputs of the process is 'Portfolio Strategic plan updates'. questions.explanation: During Develop Portfolio Charter process, the portfolio strategic plan is updated to reflect resulting changes from defining the portfolio structure. questions.text: On Efficient Frontier, where does an efficient portfolio lies (select 2 possible choices)

Along the lower bounds of the curve

An efficient portfolio can be on the lower part of the curve to the left (Cost-Minimizing portfolio)
An efficient portfolio can be on the upper part of the curve to the right (Value-Maximizing portfolio)

questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager of the City Renovation portfolio in Bin Laden organization. During which process is the portfolio structure developed and which T&T is used to develop it?

Develop Portfolio Strategic Plan, Portfolio Component Inventory

questions.text: Ms. Heena Javed is the newly appointed Governance board member in your Wedding Event portfolio in 'The Modern Organizers' company. In order to determine her roles and responsibilities, you will refer her to:
questions.explanation:
Overall explanation
Portfolio level Roles and Responsibility is decided as part of Portfolio Management plan, within Governance Model section (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 6.1.3.2 Pg# 62)

Communication Requirement Analysis (Develop Portfolio Communication plan)

- Elicitation techniques is not a correct choice here

questions.text: Which of the following artifacts can assist Executive Management to ensure that the organizational resources and capacity needed to achieve strategic objectives are in place when they are needed?
questions.explanation:
Portfolio Charter is correct, as PC has Capability & Capacity Analysis as T&T (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 4.2.2.2, Pg# 48)
